CBRE are proud to present to the market for Sale or Lease via EOI closing 10th September; Units 3&4/26-28 Napier Close, Deakin. 

The sale will be treated as a going concern and will be available as vacant possession from 1 January 2021.  

26-28 Napier close is located in the heart of Deakin which is 10 minutes South of the CBD and allows for easy access to Woden, Parliamentary Triangle and Kingston. The Deakin area has a strong medical presence, along with Government departments and many professional office users.

Building features include:
. Tremendous views to the Brindabella's
. Plenty of natural light wrapping the building
. Substantial On site car parking including secure basement spaces
. Lift access to all levels
. Disability access into the building 
. Well maintained strata building

Available for Sale or lease: 
Units 3&4 are located on the ground floor directly off the main entry point to the building. Both units combine for a total area of 508sqm* or can be subdivided down into two smaller tenancies of 235sqm* and 273sqm*. The tenancy benefits from a quality fitout in place, which includes a reception, boardroom, meeting rooms, 10 offices, open plan work stations, kitchen/break out area and a dedicated utilities area. The units benefit from 14 dedicated car bays including 8 basement bays. 

Both units are leased in one line to an accounting firm who have a lease expiring on December 31st 2020. Annual rental income for the tenancy is $220,363.63 Plus GST. 

This presents as an excellent opportunity to any tenants seeking a ready-to-occupy premises, owner occupiers/investors seeking to capitalize on the low interest rate environment or looking to own a quality office investment in a tightly held and well maintained strata building. 

For more information on this exciting opportunity please contact the exclusive sales agents at CBRE.

Approx*

CBRE are proud to bring to market Units 1-4, 17 Denison Street Deakin, a brand new building completed in 2017 which offers an excellent opportunity for savvy investors.

The units make up the ground floor of the building and are leased to Medicines Australia on a 5 year 6 month lease with 5 year option. The lease includes nine (9) basement car spaces and access to a private outdoor courtyard.

Positioned in the suburb of Deakin, known for its mix of commercial and health related occupiers, the address is centrally located in Canberra and a short distance to Barton/Parliamentary Triangle, Canberra CBD, Woden Town Centre and within 10 kilometres* of Canberra Airport. Deakin offers public transport with access to a light rail stop proposed for stage 2 as well as amenities including: Deakin Shops 1.4 kilometres* and Curtin Shops 1.7 kilometres* away. In addition, Deakin offers generous parking with public parking opposite the subject property and access to green spaces not readily available in other commercial precincts.

Key Property Features:
- 5 year 6 month lease to Medicines Australia (expiry 13 June 2024)
- Estimated Net Income of $221,000 PA
- Brand new building offering depreciation benefits
- Ample parking including 9 secure, basement car parks
- 543sqm* ground floor suite
- Short distance to Parliamentary Triangle & Canberra CBD
- Proximity to proposed future light rail stop

For further information or to arrange an inspection, please contact CBRE.

*Includes Amenities Area

Located moments from Adelaide Avenue, connecting the inner south suburb to the City and Woden area. The property is conveniently located adjacent to the post office and free public parking and offers a buyer a fitted out tenancy ready to move into and occupy.

For sale is Unit 2, a ground floor unit with fitout comprising;

- 7 functional offices
- Kitchenette
- Amenities area

The unit has direct access to;

2 showers (male and female)
2 toilets (male and female)
Which are common areas, cleaned by the body corporate.
With a separate side entrance, the unit lends itself to being split to accommodate two businesses meaning a purchaser can owner occupy on part and generate income on the remaining space.
